<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,186,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[844,989,187,213]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1043,1111,187,213]" name="Oman" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Oman</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pont, A. C." box="[1153,1286,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref35020" refString="Pont, A. C. (1991) A review of the Fanniidae and Muscidae (Diptera) of the Arabian Peninsula. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 12, 312 - 265." type="book" year="1991">Pont (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Abu-Zoherah, R. &amp; Al-Taher, K. &amp; Tilkian, S." pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref29552" refString="Abu-Zoherah, R., Al-Taher, K. &amp; Tilkian, S. (1993) List of Insects Recorded from Saudi Arabia. Ministry of Agriculture and Water, National Agriculture and Water Research Centre, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, Riyadh, 394 pp." type="book" year="1993">
Abu-Zoherah 
<emphasis box="[220,270,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. (1993)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[622,759,223,249]" name="Madagascar" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. It was recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1088,223,249]" name="Yemen" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="van Emden, F. I." box="[1103,1298,223,249]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="161 - 175" refId="ref37148" refString="van Emden, F. I. (1948) Diptera: Muscidae. In: Expedition to South-West Arabia 1937 - 1938. Vol. I. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 161 - 175." type="book chapter" year="1948">van Emden 1948</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,393]" box="[199,901,258,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,432,258,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Biological remarks.</emphasis>
Reared from cow dung (
<bibRefCitation author="Skidmore, P." box="[711,889,258,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref36277" refString="Skidmore, P. (1985) The Biology of the Muscidae of the World. Series Entomologica 29. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrecht, 550 pp." type="book" year="1985">Skidmore 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,482,294,321]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distributional Remarks</emphasis>
. Another 
<taxonomicName authority="Kowarz, 1873" authorityName="Kowarz. Several" authorityYear="1873" box="[592,695,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brontaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[592,695,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Brontaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1873" box="[795,1022,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brontaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexa">
<emphasis box="[795,879,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">B. flexa</emphasis>
Wiedemann
</taxonomicName>
, has been collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1270,1342,295,321]" name="Oman" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Oman</collectingCountry>
. The addition of these two species to the Arabian fauna doubles the number of species known from there. Some 40 species are known and occur in all zoogeographical regions but mostly the Palaeotropical.
</paragraph>
